    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Sobol global sensitivity analysis for hemolysis index predictions",
    "description": "A variance-based Sobol global sensitivity analysis was conducted across 10,000 Monte Carlo samples varying blood viscosity (±15%), turbulent dissipation rate inlet boundary condition (±25%), red blood cell damage model coefficient k (±20%), and pump rotational speed (±2%). Total-order Sobol indices identified the RBC damage model coefficient k as the dominant source of output variance (S_T = 0.61), followed by turbulent dissipation rate (S_T = 0.24); blood viscosity and rotational speed contributed marginally (S_T < 0.08 each). This analysis informed targeted experimental calibration of the damage model coefficient, reducing hemolysis index prediction uncertainty from ±38% to ±14% of the mean predicted value.",
    "method": "Sobol variance-based global sensitivity (saltelli sampler)",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "RBC damage model coefficient k",
      "Turbulent dissipation rate inlet BC"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 10000
  },
  "hasContextOfUse": {
