      "name": "Applicability constraint: centrifugal VAD hemolysis CFD domain",
      "description": "The CFD model is applicable only to continuous-flow centrifugal blood pumps operating with human whole blood (hematocrit 35–45%) at physiological temperatures (36–38 °C). The model is scoped to pump geometries with impeller tip diameters between 30 mm and 55 mm and specific speeds (Ns) between 1500 and 4500 rpm·(gpm^0.5)·(ft^-0.75). Application to axial-flow pumps, pulsatile devices, or non-Newtonian blood substitutes is explicitly out of scope."
    },
